10. h3
{ According to my database, this has not been played in the past two years. The idea is to play another prophylactic move in order to finally be able to go Nf3 and Be2 without allowing Black's ...Bg4. Initially, the engine likes this move a lot but slowly turns around later. }
10... d5
{ Breaking in the centre is the way to go.  10...e5!?  is also a move to consider as compared to9...e5 Black now has ...Bf5 and with that, an extra development move. }
11. c5 { White kicks our knight back with tempo, but that is okay. } 11... Nc8
{ The knight can be re-routed to e7 at some point. The knight looks awkward for the moment, but certainly has a future. }
12. Nge2 { Hardly ever played, yet with the idea to play g4-Bg2. } 12... Nc6
13. g4
{ Otherwise 12.Nge2 simply blocks the light-squared bishop from developing. }
13... Bd7 { Making sure the bishop is not in the way of our e-pawn. } 14. Nxd5
{ This seems a win a pawn, yet it is always dangerous to open up the position when your king is in the centre.  14.Bg2  e6  transposes to12.g4. }
14... Bxg4 { This wins back the pawn. } 15. hxg4 Qxd5 16. Rh2 e6
{ Strengthening our control of the d5-square and freeing the e7-square for our knight to come back into the game. }
17. Bg2 Qd7 18. Qd2 Rd8 19. b4 a6
{ With the last few moves, White has improved their pieces, but it's hard to break through Black's position. In a game between two youngsters, White was too eager to go forward and eventually got countered:  20.a4?!   @@StartBracket@@  20.Kf1  was probably better, putting the king a bit safer.  20...N8e7⩲  @@EndBracket@@  20...N8e7  now if  21.b5?!  axb5  22.axb5  Na7!  the b5-pawn is suddenly a target.  23.b6  Nac6⩱  White needs take care of the d4-pawn now. Instead, the game continued  @@StartFEN@@r2r2k1/1p1qnpbp/p1n1p1p1/2P5/PP1P2P1/4B3/3QNPBR/2R1K3 w - - 0 21@@EndFEN@@  21.Rd1  Nd5  22.Rb1  e5!  and, with White wasting a few moves, Black went on to win the game: Munshi,A @@StartBracket@@2133@@EndBracket@@-Manafov,V @@StartBracket@@2245@@EndBracket@@ Porto Carras 2018. }
*

