{ And we can continue our centre play with moves like ...Nc6-...Re8 and ...d5. For example: }
12. Nf3 Nc6 13. Nb5
{ A nice move to try and keep the position closed.  13.Be2  d5⩱  0-1 @@StartBracket@@28@@EndBracket@@ Zatonskih, A @@StartBracket@@2447@@EndBracket@@ -Fier,A @@StartBracket@@2544@@EndBracket@@ Amsterdam 2018 }
13... d5 14. c5 Nd7 { The knight on b5 covers d4. } 15. Be2 Qa5+
{ We have other ways of continuing the pressure. This move targets the a2-pawn, and therefore White has to trade queens. }
