{ Our bishop is trapped again. } 13... Bxd5
{ Sacrificing the bishop for two pawns. } 14. cxd5 Nxd5 15. Qd2
{ My suggestion for White. I think it's a good idea to give the exchange back in order to have a more comfortable development. }
15... Nxc3 16. Qxc3 d5 17. h4
{ To get the white rook into play and stop the black queen's check on h4.  17.f4?  Qh4+  . }
17... e5 { White cannot take the pawn as ...Re8 will just win a piece. } 18.
Qd2 Nc6 19. h5 Rc8
{ With a double-edged position. Both players have chances to win here. } *

