At first, my engine likes White, yet soon it turns and assesses this position as only slightly better for White. So, this line is definitely worth a closer look. And, if anything, White will have a hard time finding all the defensive moves. }
10. Bd3
{ A solid approach that could easily be underestimated. With this move White solves a lot of tactical problems. }
10... Bxd3 11. Qxd3 d5 { As usual, we want to undermine the centre. } 12. c5
Nc8 13. Nf3 Nc6
{ 13...b6?  doesn't do much, unfortunately. Taking on c5 is not a good idea at the moment, as White can start pushing passed pawns on the queenside.  14.O-O  bxc5?!  15.dxc5±  . }
14. O-O e6 { Making room for our knight to jump to f5. } 15. a3
