20. Bf1 { Also an improvement over the game. } 20... fxg4 21. Rh2
{ Activating the rook, finally. } 21... Na4 22. Nxa4
{ White manages to trade off or activate some pieces. } 22... Rxa4 23. Rc7
Raxf4 { A strong intermezzo. } 24. Be2 Bf5 25. hxg4 Bxg4 26. Rxe7 h5
{ We still have excellent compensation for the piece. The computer indicates that White has a slight advantage. I would say the drawing margin is quite large as Black's pawns on the kingside are very dangerous, and White still needs to deal with a lot of threats. }
