O-O 9. b3 Bf5
{ In this second chapter, we are going to take a look at the more natural way of playing for White, focusing on quick development. }
10. Be2 d5 11. c5 Nc8 12. g4
{ Only played a handful of times, yet it is always an interesting idea for White to kick our bishop back from its good post on f5. }
12... Bd7
{ Now  13.Nxd5??  loses a piece again to  13...Bc6!  .   For  13.f4!?  Nc6  14.h4  seethe 13.h4 line. }
