13... exd4 14. Bxd4 Bxd4 15. Qxd4 Nc6 { Developing with tempo. } 16. Qd2
{ Aside from f4, this is also a good square for the queen. } 16... Nb4
{ Threatening to win an exchange with ...Nd3. } 17. Bc4
{ Protecting against ...Nd3. } 17... Qxd2+ 18. Kxd2 Ne7
{ And Black has more than enough compensation for the pawn. } *

