17... Nxc5
{ 17...Ne7?!  was a serious inaccuracy in the game Sarakauskas,G @@StartBracket@@2433@@EndBracket@@-Navarro Cia,M @@StartBracket@@2256@@EndBracket@@ Daventry 2020.  18.Bf3!  Nxc5  19.O-O  exf2+  Our knight on e7 is unable to move, which, compared to the text, gives us no initiative. White is now more or less a full exchange up.  20.Kh1  Rd2  with at least some kind of initiative, is better than the game, which continued  20...Nd3?  21.Rcd1  g5  compared to the mainline 17...Nxc5, this doesn't make much sense without the other knight on d6.  22.g4  Bg6  23.Be4!+-  and White is already winning. }
18. O-O exf2+ 19. Rxf2 Ne7 { Now this is a useful in-between move. } 20. Bf3
Nd3 21. Rd1 Rc8
{ Attacking the f2-rook with our d3-knight and attacking c3 with both our bishop and rook. We will win the sacrificed material back with a slightly better position thanks to the bishop pair. }
