17. Qc2 { 17.Bd3?  is bad due to  17...Nxb2  . } 17... f4
{ With a little trap in mind, if you will. White could win a piece now by playing  18.b4  , right?   17...Qd7??  blunders a piece. The tactical justification of White's previous move is that b4 is now possible as the knight on c3 is protected.  18.b4+-  . }
18. Rae1 Ne5 19. Qf5 Nb3
{ Another point of @@StartFEN@@r2q1rk1/pp2ppb1/1n1p3p/n2P1p2/P6B/2N4P/1P2BPP1/R2Q1RK1 b - - 1 16@@EndFEN@@  16...Nbc4  . The knight on b3 suddenly is very active.   19...Ng6  20.Bd3  Nb3  transposes. }
20. Kh1 { This loses an important tempo. } 20... Ng6
{ Trapping the bishop on h4. } 21. Bd3 Nd4 22. Qg4 Nxh4 23. Qxh4 e5
{ Black is a pawn up and has no problems. } *

