11... Ne5 { As I said, the knight is quite stable here. } 12. Be2 Bf5 13. Nf3
Nxf3+
{ 13...Ng4?!  is less good:  14.Bd4  and you could argue that the knight on g4 is a bit clumsy. The knight is in the way of the f5-bishop, while the knight on f3 has potential on d4 or on g5. }
14. Bxf3 Nd7
{ A logical move, in my opinion. The knight looks stable on e5 and afterwards, we can think of ideas connected to the queenside with ...a6-...b5, for example. }
