{ This knight covers the d5-square to enable ...Qc7 followed by ...Nd7xc5.   13...Ndxc5?  14.Rd1  and the Black queen can't comfortably go to b6 or c7 due to Nd5. Black is in trouble.   13...Naxc5?!  14.Rd1  with very good compensation for the pawn in the game: Kupreichik,V @@StartBracket@@2447@@EndBracket@@-Uryupin,I @@StartBracket@@2223@@EndBracket@@ Tambov 2010. }
14. O-O { 14.Rd1  Qc7  . } 14... Qc7
{ And we can decide on the next move if we want to take the pawn or play ...Ne5 and finish our development. }
