12. Na3
{ If  12.Nbd2?!  the knight is awkwardly placed here in front of the c1-bishop. After  12...Nxb3  13.Qxb3  Nd7=  followed by ...b5-...Bb7, for example, we have good counterplay as White is not in time with the Be3-Bd4 manoeuvre. }
