Be6 19. Nc5 Bd5
{ White can try to take the pawn here, but that will be quite dangerous. } 20.
Nxc4 Nxc4 21. Bxc4 Bxc4 22. Nxb7 Rd3
{ And Black will win the pawn back with the advantage of the bishop pair. } *

