11... Re8 12. Qd2
{ This has only been played once. White is trying to force the trade on b3, activating his rook on a1 and keeping the option open to still play Nc3. The Nc3-idea is quite annoying here and we have to find a plan other than ...e5. }
12... Nbc4
{ With this move we have an active idea in ...b5 and ...Bb7.  12...Nac4!?  is a decent alternative, but once again after  13.Qc1  I struggle to find an active plan for Black. White will play a4-a5 and Nc3 with a very easy position to play.   12...Nxb3?!  13.axb3±  is very pleasant for White and Black will struggle to find an active plan. }
13. Bxc4 { There is no reason for White to exchange the bishop yet. } 13...
Nxc4 14. Qb4 Nb6 15. c4 Bf5
{ ...b5 is no longer happening and with this move Black has many ideas. For example, to play ...d5, ...e5, or to put pressure on the c-pawn with ...Rc8. }
