10. Nc3 { This is now a good move. } 10... Nd4 { Targeting c2. } 11. Qd1
{ The only way to protect c2 comfortably. } 11... Qd7
{ 11...Ra5?  12.f4  doesn't help Black much in this case. The text is a fantastic move whose idea is easy to explain. If we have to move the knight away from d4, White will no longer take on d8 preventing us from ever castling - with the queen on d7, we can now recapture with the c8-bishop. The position is roughly equal. For example: }
12. Be3 Nf5
{ A further illustration of the point of our previous move. Our knight can move to f5 without having to worry about the trade of queens. }
*

