[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "4.2) White plays an early Bc4 - 3.Bc4"]
[Black "Early Bc4 lines - Alapin Sicilian move order"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. c3 Nf6 3. e5 Nd5 4. Bc4 Nb6 5. Bb3 c4 { 5...d6  6.exd6  . } 6. Bc2
Nc6 7. Nf3 d6 8. exd6 Qxd6
{ This is the Alapin Sicilian move order I will mention in this chapter. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "4.2) White plays an early Bc4 - 3.Bc4"]
[Black "Early Bc4 lines - 3.g3 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. g3 { This is sometimes played as well. } 3... d6 4. exd6
Qxd6
{ I like this better than  4...exd6  , although that is certainly a good move as well. }
5. Bg2 Nc6 6. Nc3
{ 6.Ne2?!  prepares Nc3 but is passive. After  6...e5  7.Nbc3  Be6∓  Black has a much better position, with the centre under control. We'll castle long and retreat the queen to d7 to enable ...Bc5-...Bb6, with ideas like ...h5-...h4. }
6... Nxc3 7. dxc3
{ The wrong recapture. The main line is  7.bxc3  bringing a pawn into the centre and not allowing Black's reply. }
7... Qxd1+ 8. Kxd1 Bg4+ 9. Ke1 e5
{ And since White can't castle, Black has the advantage. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "4.2) White plays an early Bc4 - 3.Bc4"]
[Black "Early Bc4 lines - 3.g3 #2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. g3 { This is sometimes played as well. } 3... d6 4. exd6
Qxd6
{ I like this better than  4...exd6  , although that is certainly a good move as well. }
5. Bg2 Nc6 6. Nc3
{ 6.Ne2?!  prepares Nc3 but is passive. After  6...e5  7.Nbc3  Be6∓  Black has a much better position, with the centre under control. We'll castle long and retreat the queen to d7 to enable ...Bc5-...Bb6, with ideas like ...h5-...h4. }
6... Nxc3 7. bxc3 e5 { Grabbing space in the centre. } 8. d3 Be7 9. Ne2
{ The knight is kind of misplaced here. } 9... Be6 10. c4 Qd7
{ Trying to exchange the strong light-squared bishop on g2. } 11. Rb1 O-O-O 12.
O-O Bh3
{ Black was very comfortable in: Petrosian,T @@StartBracket@@2606@@EndBracket@@-Nakamura,H @@StartBracket@@2670@@EndBracket@@ Gibraltar 2008. }
*

