5. Bg2 Nc6 6. Nc3
{ 6.Ne2?!  prepares Nc3 but is passive. After  6...e5  7.Nbc3  Be6∓  Black has a much better position, with the centre under control. We'll castle long and retreat the queen to d7 to enable ...Bc5-...Bb6, with ideas like ...h5-...h4. }
6... Nxc3 7. bxc3 e5 { Grabbing space in the centre. } 8. d3 Be7 9. Nf3
