{ Simply attacking the e5-pawn, which White has a hard time defending. } 15.
Qf4 Qe7 16. Rfe1 { Not the right rook, as we'll see. } 16... Nxe5
{ Now we can simply take the pawn. } 17. Nxe5 Qxe5 18. Bh5
{ This is why White needed to move to e1 the other rook. } 18... Qxe1+
{ Unfortunately for White, now it's checkmate in 2. } *

