{ 16...f6!?  also wins back the pawn.  17.Nf7!  Kxf7  18.Bd3  Kg8  19.Rfe1=∞  leaves White with a dangerous initiative for the pawn. }
17. Qxf6 gxf6
{ And we win the pawn back with an equal position. There is still some fight left here, so no time to relax. }
