6... Nxc3
{ 6...d6  7.cxd6  cxd6  8.Nf3  is a transposition to the Alapin with Nc3. } 7.
bxc3 b6 { The way to play if we don't want to transpose. } 8. cxb6
{ Played 80% of the time, but Black gets easy play. } 8... axb6 9. Nf3 Be7
{ We develop our kingside before moving our light-squared bishop.  9...Ba3!?Ν  looks like a very pleasant alternative. We have a simple development plan with ...Qe7, ...Bb7 and ...Nc6.   9...Bb7!?  is very calm and collected. We develop and then break with ...d6.  10.Bd3  Be7  11.O-O  O-O  12.Qe2  d6⇆  followed by ...Nbd7. }
10. Bd3 { The ideal place for the bishop. } 10... Ba6
{ Exchanging the strong d3-bishop. } 11. Bxa6 { Here White has lost a tempo. }
11... Nxa6
{ And we can re-route our knight to c7 @@StartBracket@@and d5@@EndBracket@@ after playing ...c5. }
