1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. c4 Nb6 4. c5 Nd5 5. Nc3 e6 6. Bc4
{ This move signifies a pawn sacrifice I have often faced in blitz games. The idea is to offer the c5-pawn to speed up development. }
6... Bxc5
{ Much less played than  6...Nxc3  , yet just as good. I deliberated which line to recommend and decided this was the more practical choice, as it is newer and, therefore, less likely for White to know. }
7. d4 Nxc3 8. bxc3 Bf8
{ This should be fine for Black. We anticipate White's Qg4 and we will follow up with moves like ...d5 and ...c5 to start gaining space. For example: }
9. Bd3 d5 10. Qg4 b6 { Intending to trade our bad light-squared bishop. } *

