[Black "The practical 4.c5 - Alternative to 6...Bxc5 #2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. c4 Nb6 4. c5 Nd5 5. Nc3 e6 6. Bc4
{ This move signifies a pawn sacrifice I have often faced in blitz games. The idea is to offer the c5-pawn to speed up development. }
6... Nxc3
{ The mainline, which has been played much more often thanmy recommendation,  which is  6...Bxc5!?  . }
7. dxc3
{ 7.bxc3?!  d5!  It is the perfect time for this move.  8.cxd6  cxd6  9.exd6  Bxd6  10.Nf3  O-O  with a very good version of the Alapin for Black.Instead,  @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/pppp1ppp/4p3/2P1P3/2B5/2P5/P2P1PPP/R1BQK1NR b KQkq - 0 7@@EndFEN@@  7...Bxc5  8.d4=∞  leads to your typical compensation for White. }
7... Nc6
{ 7...Bxc5?!  is what White is hoping for.  8.Qg4!=∞  and White gets tremendous compensation for the pawn. It didn't take me long to figure out that we should avoid this line. }
8. Bf4
{ 8.Qh5!?  is another move that poses Black a lot of problems. It hasn't been played often, but it's another reason to go for5...Bxc5, as it could get us into trouble.  8...Bxc5  9.Nf3  with typical compensation for the pawn. Black struggles to break free.  9...d5  10.Bd3=∞  . }
8... Qh4
{ A move I like very much. We play for a trick, and if White responds correctly, it still leaves them with some weaknesses.   8...Bxc5!?  9.Qg4  g5!  is another funny option, solving the g-pawn problem and going for an endgame, and now:A@@EndBracket@@  10.Qxg5?  Qxg5  11.Bxg5  Nxe5  12.Be2  Be7∓  and Black is a solid pawn up but after  @@StartFEN@@r1b1k2r/pppp1p1p/4p3/2b1n1B1/2B5/2P5/PP3PPP/R3K1NR w KQkq - 0 12@@EndFEN@@  12.Bf6  Nxc4  13.Bxh8  Nxb2∓  we have two pawns for the exchange and a much better pawn structure. Black is clearly better.B@@EndBracket@@  @@StartFEN@@r1bqk2r/pppp1p1p/2n1p3/2b1P1p1/2B2BQ1/2P5/PP3PPP/R3K1NR w KQkq - 0 10@@EndFEN@@  10.Bxg5  Rg8!  pinning the bishop.  11.h4  A good move to include.   @@StartBracket@@  11.Bxd8?!  Rxg4  and both bishops are under attack.  12.Be2  Rxg2  13.Bxc7  a5  is similar to the line after 11.h4, yet the inclusion of h4 and ...h6 would benefit White, in my opinion.@@EndBracket@@  11...h6  12.Bxd8  Rxg4  13.Be2  Rxg2  14.Bxc7  a5!?Ν  with a complicated position, but objectively Black is fine. Also possible are  14...Rxf2!?  or  14...b5!?  .   8...g5!?  9.Bg3  h5  might be fun to try out as well. }
9. Qd2 Nxe5
{ This is the trick I mentioned. We win a pawn thanks to the pin on the f4-bishop. }
