{ The second most played move besides  9.Bb3  , covered inthe previous chapter. White is trying to solidify the centre, protecting the d4-pawn, before doing anything else. The c4 push may still be tried at some point, but it has been postponed for now. }
9... Nd7 { Developing and offering a knight trade. } 10. Nd3
{ Not a bad place for the knight. It keeps an eye out for the ...c5-break. Therefore, a sensible approach for us is not to try and play on the queenside too much. }
10... Re8 { Aiming to play ...e5. } 11. Bg5 { The only good way to stop it. }
11... N7b6 12. Bb3 Bf5
{ The bishop is nicely aimed at the d3-knight, hindering the b1-knight's development. Our long-term idea is still ...e5. }
