{ This pawn structure is not so bad for Black. As long as White cannot use his pawn majority on the queenside, we are fine. The a5-pawn plays an important role there, as now every queenside pawn break has a drawback for White. Notice how the f6-pawn also keeps the d3-knight off the e5-square. }
