{ And Black will most like win back the pawn. Notice how, thanks to the @@StartFEN@@r1b1r1k1/ppn2pbp/2p3p1/2n1P1B1/2P5/5N2/PPB2PPP/RN2R1K1 b - - 3 15@@EndFEN@@  15...N7a6  16.a3  inclusion, the c5-knight has an extra square on b3. Preferably, we just win the e5-pawn back, of course. }
