8... Bg7 9. O-O O-O 10. Bb3
{ This is unnecessary. Black wasn't threatening anything. } 10... Nd7
{ As usual, we welcome minor piece trades. For example,  11.Nxd7  Qxd7  12.Nxd5  Bxd5  13.Bxd5  cxd5  14.c3  b5⇆  and we can launch our minority attack.A move like  @@StartFEN@@r4rk1/pp1qppbp/2p1b1p1/3n4/3P4/1BN2Q2/PPP2PPP/R1B2RK1 w - - 0 12@@EndFEN@@  12.h3?!  gets White into trouble:  12...Nb4  attacks d4 and, indirectly, also c2. }
