12. cxb5 { 12.Nc3?  bxc4  13.Bxc4  Nb6  and White loses a whole pawn. } 12...
Bb7 13. Nc3 Nxd5
{ This is an extra option we don't have in the 11...Nxd3 line. Instead of taking the bishop on d3, we immediately win the pawn back. }
14. Nxd5 { 14.Bd2  e6⇆  with a roughly equal position. } 14... Bxd5 15. Bg5 Re8
16. Bf1 Nb6
{ This looks extremely pleasant for Black thanks to our strong bishops. } *

