1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. d4 d6 4. Nf3 dxe5 5. Nxe5 g6 6. Be2
{ Another move that happened in the Firouzja-Carlsen match in 2020. The idea is to castle before playing c4. }
6... Bg7
{ Once again, we don't have to play ...c6 here as there is no threat. } 7. O-O
O-O 8. c3 { This allows us to execute our preferred break. } 8... c5 9. Nf3
cxd4 10. Nxd4 Nc6
{ Allowing our pawn structure to be slightly damaged is perfectly OK. Black gets a lot of active play in return. }
11. Nxc6 bxc6 12. Bf3 Rb8
{ This happened in the game: Vachier Lagrave,M @@StartBracket@@2784@@EndBracket@@-Carlsen,M @@StartBracket@@2862@@EndBracket@@ Chess.com INT 2020. I imagine Carlsen was very happy here. }
*

