1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. d4 d6 4. Nf3 dxe5 5. Nxe5 g6 6. Be2
{ Another move that happened in the Firouzja-Carlsen match in 2020. The idea is to castle before playing c4. }
6... Bg7
{ Once again, we don't have to play ...c6 here as there is no threat. } 7. O-O
O-O 8. c3 { This allows us to execute our preferred break. } 8... c5 9. Bf3
cxd4 10. Qxd4
{ 10.cxd4  Nc6⩱  with a similar approach as in the MVL-Carlsen game mentionedhere. Damaging our pawn structure slightly gives us active play in return. }
10... Nc6 11. Nxc6 bxc6 12. Qh4 e5 13. Qxd8 Rxd8 14. Na3 f5
{ Firouzja,A @@StartBracket@@2702@@EndBracket@@-Carlsen,M @@StartBracket@@2876@@EndBracket@@ chess24.com INT 2020 ended in a draw in 52 moves. I imagine Carlsen was pleased in this position too. }
