[White "7.6) The Classic Nf3 Variation - 6.Be2"]
[Black "Classic - 8.Nf3 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. d4 d6 4. Nf3 dxe5 5. Nxe5 g6 6. Be2
{ Another move that happened in the Firouzja-Carlsen match in 2020. The idea is to castle before playing c4. }
6... Bg7
{ Once again, we don't have to play ...c6 here as there is no threat. } 7. O-O
O-O 8. Nf3
{ This has occurred a few times, and also in an internet game of yours truly. The knight retreats as prophylaxis against our ...c5.  8.c4  Nb6  9.Nc3  will transpose tothe previous chapter on 6.c4. }
8... Nc6
{ Developing normally and making use of the fact that we didn't have to play ...c6. }
9. Re1 { This leads to immediate equality. } 9... Nb6
{ Threatening to win the d4-pawn. } 10. c3 { 10.Be3  e5!  is similar. } 10...
e5 11. dxe5 Nxe5 12. Nxe5 Bxe5 { And the position is completely equal. } *

