{ This is therefore my suggestion. We want to get rid of the e5-knight and start targeting the d4-pawn.   8...O-O?!  has been played before.  9.Qd2!Ν  scares me a bit. White wants to protect the d4-pawn with Rd1 before developing the kingside. For example:A:@@EndBracket@@  9...Be6  10.b3  N8d7  11.Qe3!  and once again, it's hard to find a breakthrough.B:@@EndBracket@@  @@StartFEN@@rnbq1rk1/ppp1ppbp/1n4p1/4N3/2PP1B2/2N5/PP1Q1PPP/R3KB1R b KQ - 0 9@@EndFEN@@  9...N8d7  10.Qe3  Nxe5  11.Bxe5  Bxe5  12.Qxe5±  followed by Be2 and O-O and White has a clear space-advantage.C:@@EndBracket@@  @@StartFEN@@rnbq1rk1/ppp1ppbp/1n4p1/4N3/2PP1B2/2N5/PP1Q1PPP/R3KB1R b KQ - 0 9@@EndFEN@@  9...Nc6  10.Nxc6  bxc6  11.Rd1!+-  and I have trouble finding a breakthrough with Black.  11...Be6  12.b3  Qd7  13.Qe3  . }
