{ We want to undermine White's centre as soon as possible.  8...O-O?!  This gives White the option to solve the problem of the d4-pawn.  9.Qb3!  and now many options as possible, such as  9...Be6!?  ,  9...Nc6!?  or  9...c5  10.Rd1  solidifying the d4-pawn.  10...cxd4  11.Bxd4  Qe8  12.c5  and I would not want to play this position. }
