{ 8...Qd7!?Ν  could be quite clever as well. White is waiting for us to play ...Nc6. Well, then we wait for White's light-squared bishop to move first. }
9. c3
{ This is quite a clever way for White to play, taking away the b4- and d4-squares away from our knights. }
9... Qd7 10. Bb5 { 10.Be2  O-O-O  11.O-O  h5⇆  with a nice kingside attack. }
10... O-O-O 11. O-O Nde7
{ Followed by ...Qd5 and ...Nf5 with great play for Black. } *

