8. Nf3 f5
{ This is a suggestion from my engine to break in the centre as soon as possible. }
9. exf6 { 9.Nf2  Bc5  and the bishop looks wonderful on c5. } 9... Nxf6 10. Bd3
{ 10.Nxf6+?  Qxf6  is already excellent for Black as we can castle long on the next move. }
10... Nb4
{ With complications. We are trying to force White to exchange on f6. Play is difficult, but I do think White faces some difficult choices. }
