1. e4 Nf6 2. Nc3
{ White decides not to delve into the deeps of the Alekhine waters and instead chooses the calmer and safer  2.Nc3  . Black has many good options here. }
2... d5
{ The only line with independent value. I like playing  2...e5  because I have a lot of experience in 1.e4 e5  from the black side. The most dangerous lines occur after 2.Nf3. With this move order, we have avoided them.  3.Nf3  Nc6  The Four Knights Opening and no problem for Black according to current theory.  3...d6!?  was my choice if I wanted a complicated game. We usually transpose to the Black Lion, on which Simon Williams, a.k.a. GingerGM, has published an excellent course here on Chessable.  4.d4  Nbd7  transposes to the Black Lion. }
