{ White has some problems to solve. Taking on c6 is still not possible - we can simply recapture with our d7-bishop and win the d2-bishop. For example: }
13. Bxb4 Qxb4+ 14. Qd2 Qxd2+ 15. Kxd2 Nd4
{ Black is threatening ...g5 winning the h4-knight. } 16. g3 Nxe2 17. Kxe2 c6
18. dxc6 Bg4+
{ Black is already winning - the white king is too exposed, and the knight on h4 is dominated by our bishop. }
